                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The Hottest Gift of 1993 Was My Gateway to Technology]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-hottest-gift-of-1993-was-my-gateway-to-technology/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Joe Fedewa]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/talkboy-deluxe-hero.jpg" length="349" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Hobbies]]></category><category><![CDATA[physical media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Tech Throwback]]></category><category><![CDATA[Home Alone 2: Lost in New York]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            "Credit card? You got it!"
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>It’s 1993, and the Holiday season is in full swing. <em>Mrs. Doubtfire</em> is on the big screen, and <em>Doom</em> is about to become an overnight smash hit. However, a 5-year-old boy has his heart set on something else. A movie prop that became a real toy—the Talkboy Deluxe.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 09 Sep 2025 12:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-hottest-gift-of-1993-was-my-gateway-to-technology/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[5 Best Linux Distros for Playing AAA Windows Games]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-distros-for-playing-aaa-windows-games/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Dibakar Ghosh]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/tux-the-linux-mascot-wearing-headphones-and-holding-a-game-controller-in-front-of-the-word-gaming-on-a-purple-background.png" length="4005" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Gaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            You haven't experienced Linux gaming if you haven't gamed on these distros!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Want to play Windows games on your Linux computer but don't know where to start? Did you hear some Linux distros are better suited for gaming but don't know which ones to try? Well, here's a list going over the five best Linux distros that can help you play AAA Windows games.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 09 Sep 2025 11:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-distros-for-playing-aaa-windows-games/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[8BitDo Arcade Controller Review: All-Button Design and Pro Layout]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/8bitdo-arcade-controller-review/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bill Loguidice]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/01-2025-09-06-14-46-53.jpg" length="538" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[8BitDo Arcade Controller]]></category><category><![CDATA[controllers]]></category><category><![CDATA[xbox]]></category><category><![CDATA[Nintendo Switch]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The 8BitDo Arcade Controller features a sleek, all-button leverless design and a precision quad-movement layout.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>All-button controllers promise greater precision, speed, and comfort, particularly for fighting games. Although its use cases have limits, the <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0F7RMB4RH?tag=hotoge-20&ascsubtag=UUhtgUeUpU2016337&asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2F8bitdo-arcade-controller-review%2F&asc_campaign=Authority" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">8BitDo Arcade Controller</a> is an affordable and, more importantly, quality way to game in this unique way.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 09 Sep 2025 10:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/8bitdo-arcade-controller-review/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Signal Finally Gets A Long-Awaited Feature]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/signal-finally-gets-a-long-awaited-feature/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/signal-backups-hero.jpg" length="164" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Signal]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            We've been waiting for this. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Signal has managed to position itself as a strong competitor to WhatsApp and similar apps, but it lacks one very important thing—cloud backups. Now, we have them, though they work a bit differently from how backups work in other apps.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 08 Sep 2025 22:05:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/signal-finally-gets-a-long-awaited-feature/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The Best Free-to-Play Games on PlayStation 5]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/best-free-to-play-games-playstation-5/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tim Brookes]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/playstation-5-ps5-dualsense-controller.jpg" length="4753" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[PlayStation]]></category><category><![CDATA[PlayStation 5]]></category><category><![CDATA[games]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Free-to-play has no limits.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The PlayStation Store is full of games, and a surprising number of them are free to play. Not all are worth your time, however, so we’ve taken the liberty of rounding up a few of our favorites.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 08 Sep 2025 22:00:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/best-free-to-play-games-playstation-5/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Cheap Charging Cables: The Hidden Dangers Revealed]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/hidden-dangers-of-cheap-charging-cables/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/shutterstock_2499509809.jpg" length="312" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[USB-C]]></category><category><![CDATA[Cybersecurity]]></category><category><![CDATA[USB]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Cheap is expensive, don't you know?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>We all need charging cables, and the costs can add up quickly. So it's tempting to simply order the cheapest cables you can find and call it a day. However, saving a few dollars on charging cables can end up costing you much more than it saves you in the short term.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 08 Sep 2025 21:31:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/hidden-dangers-of-cheap-charging-cables/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[If I Only Had $400 for a Work PC, Here’s What I’d Do]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/if-i-only-had-400-for-a-work-pc-heres-what-id-do/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ismar Hrnjicevic]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/52844692712_16be54b0a6_o.jpg" length="269" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[laptops]]></category><category><![CDATA[pc building]]></category><category><![CDATA[Ajazz AK820]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            $400 can buy you plenty of productivity if you know where to look.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you need a new work computer and have a tight budget of only $400, it might seem like an impossible task. However, if you know where and how to spend your money, you can build a surprisingly capable workstation setup. Here’s what I’d do with that budget.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 08 Sep 2025 21:01:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/if-i-only-had-400-for-a-work-pc-heres-what-id-do/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Linux ip Command: 7 Practical Usage Examples]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/uses-for-the-linux-ip-command/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jordan Gloor]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/tux-the-linux-mascot-holding-an-ethernet-cable-with-networking-icons-around.png" length="602" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux & macOS Terminal]]></category><category><![CDATA[Wi-Fi Routers]]></category><category><![CDATA[Cloud & Internet]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            You can do more than just check your IP address.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Ever wondered what <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/657911/how-to-use-the-ip-command-on-linux/" target="_blank">the Linux ip command</a> might be able to do for you? Maybe you're just getting into Linux terminal work or network management. Let me walk you through some basic examples of the ip command at work.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 08 Sep 2025 21:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/uses-for-the-linux-ip-command/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Cross-Platform Play: A Gamer's Nightmare? Why I Avoid It]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/reasons-i-always-avoid-cross-platform-multiplayer/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/shutterstock_2455673583.jpg" length="297" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Gaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[mouse]]></category><category><![CDATA[Online Gaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Let's all just stay in our lanes.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I'm not much of an online multiplayer gamer, preferring to play single-player games, or sticking to local multiplayer with people I know.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 08 Sep 2025 20:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/reasons-i-always-avoid-cross-platform-multiplayer/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Robot Sports: Humanoid Athletes Compete in Groundbreaking Games]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/your-next-favorite-athlete-may-be-a-robot/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Aran Folsom]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/humanoid-robots-sprinting-on-a-blue-running-track-in-a-stadium-with-the-title-world-humanoid-robot-games-whrg-displayed-at-the-top.png" length="1954" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Cutting Edge]]></category><category><![CDATA[Robotics]]></category><category><![CDATA[ai]]></category><category><![CDATA[Sports]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            These humanoids are running, jumping, and dancing their way into the world of sports.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>This year marked the first-ever international sporting event to feature humanoid robots as athletes. These robots, with some help from the humans behind their creation, competed against each other in the World Humanoid Robot Games to showcase the athletic and practical abilities these machines possess.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 08 Sep 2025 19:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/your-next-favorite-athlete-may-be-a-robot/</guid></item></channel>
